Assad Says Changes to Be Made to Syrian Constitution as Crackdown Persists

-- B y   Z a i d   S a b a h   A b d   A l h a m i d
-- 
2011-08-21T18:14:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-21/assad-says-changes-to-be-made-to-syrian-constitution-as-crackdown-persists.html
Syrian President Bashar al-Assad,
seeking to end five months of violence, said talks are ongoing
to make changes to the country’s constitution.   Assad said the country’s security situation has improved
and that the government would be tough on terrorists.  He spoke in an interview on state television
from Damascus.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zaid Sabah Abd Alhamid in Washington at 
 zalhamid@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  